                    Transmitted to the Ambassador in China for
                        delivery to Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d370</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">370</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-08-23T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="370" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Nanking Embassy Files, Lot F–73: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to President
                            <persName type="to">Chiang Kai-shek</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="33" xml:id="d370fn33">Transmitted to the Ambassador in China for
                        delivery to Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-23">August 23,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[White House No. 338.] Please accept this expression of my appreciation of your
                    considerate action in regard to the surrender of the Japanese in Hong Kong to a
                    British commander by which action you eased a difficult situation.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
